 the pledge of allegiance because of it being Christian yet it says ‘and justice for all’ there isn’t. Last I checked this wasn’t only a Christian country. It didn’t have its own religion. Sure Christianity was and is popular. I don’t care. There is Muslims and satanists and people who worship a toad at my school. I still love them. They’re my friends and I don’t care if they’re black white Asian or freakin Mexican. I don’t judge by religion, race, or gender. Unlike the bible. Do you guys even read it? Read it and you’ll change your mind on this whole religion thing. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="881" language="en" documentId="1835" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Seth Leachman" date="03/07/2013 12:52 AM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://www.forerunner.com/forerunner/X0098_Ban_on_school_prayer.html#c003649" topic="prayer-in-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="1835" notes="" title="Banning Prayer in Public Schools Has Led to America's Demise"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="881"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>